      "content": "It's completely natural to be apprehensive about healthcare systems, especially when past experiences have been disappointing. Pulling out some of your prescription anxiety medication to help you relax could be a temporary measure, but it's important to consider the risks, such as dependency, side effects, or interactions with other substances that might exacerbate your feelings of discomfort. If you're contemplating this choice, ensuring you have reachable health insurance information or contacts in Dubai would be a good idea to avoid further complications. If your symptoms don’t subside or worsen, you might want to try to find a local clinic that can offer more accessible care, perhaps one geared towards women, who may feel more comfortable discussing your concerns. If possible, take some time to talk to a hotline for travel-related health issues; they can often provide good guidance and reassurance. Remember that getting professional medical advice is worth the effort, especially when in doubt, and it won't necessarily cost you as much as you fear.",
